dn.net/v1/article/detail/149235122\"}]\n\nI searched for AI coding and developer tools launched on Product Hunt in February 2025 and March 2025. However, I wasn't able to find specific tools with exact launch dates matching those criteria.\n\n## Summary of Findings\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about AI coding/developer tools around early 2025:\n\n### Tools Discussed in Early 2025 Context:\n\n1. **Claude Code** - Agent coding tool launched by Anthropic (references suggest launch around February 2025)\n   - Terminal-based AI coding agent\n   - Understands codebases and executes routine tasks\n   - Handles git workflows through natural language commands\n\n2. **OpenAI Developer Tools** - Released March 12, 2025\n   - New Responses API\n   - Three built-in tools\n   - Open-source Agents SDK\n   - Aimed at simplifying agent development\n\n3. **DeepSeek-Coder** - Featured in 2025 roundups\n   - Open-source AI programming tool\n   - Based on Mixture-of-Experts (MoE) architecture\n   - Strong code generation and completion capabilities\n\n4. **GitHub Spark** - Mentioned as a 2025 Microsoft release\n   - Generates complete React+TypeScript applications from natural language\n   - 20-second app generation capability\n\n### Notable 2025 AI Programming Tools Frequently Mentioned:\n- **Cursor** (with 4.0 updates in 2025)\n- **Windsurf** (AI-driven IDE)\n- **Augment Code**\n- **Trae AI**\n- **Qwen3-Coder** (Alibaba)\n\n**Note:** The search results primarily discussed tools in the context of 2025 trends and roundups, but didn't provide specific Product Hunt launch dates for February or March 2025. Most sources were retrospective articles about AI coding tools in 2025 rather than specific launch announcements.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
