per Peter Steinberger\n- **Core features**: Local-first AI agent platform that executes real tasks (file operations, browser control, email, scheduling, coding) through WhatsApp, Telegram, Discord, and other chat platforms\n- **Architecture**: All data, memory, and operations processed locally on user devices (Mac/Windows/Linux/mobile/servers) - no cloud uploads\n\n## **PicoClaw - Lightweight Go Implementation**\n\n**Launch Date: February 9, 2026**\n- **Built in just 1 day** to bring AI agents to $10 hardware with <10MB RAM\n- **Rapid adoption**: 5,000 GitHub stars within 4 days (during Chinese New Year)\n- **Developer**: sipeed team\n- **Technology**: Go language rewrite of OpenClaw\n- **Advantages vs OpenClaw**: \n  - Memory: <10MB (vs >1GB)\n  - Startup time: <1 second (vs >500 seconds)\n  - Hardware cost: As low as $10 (vs $599 Mac Mini)\n\n## **OpenCode - Integration Launch**\n\n**February 2, 2026 Integration:**\n- Integrated into **Ollama v0.15.4** with the command `ollama launch openclaw`\n- Automated onboarding process introduced\n- OpenClaw \"took over\" Clawdbot functionality\n- Enhanced tool parsing capabilities for local AI deployment\n\n## **Additional Context**\n- Over 300 derivative projects have emerged on GitHub\n- Major cloud providers (Tencent Cloud, Alibaba Cloud, JD Cloud, Baidu Cloud) launched one-click OpenClaw deployment services\n- The project has become a \"phenomenal\" open-source success in the AI agent space\n\nAll three projects appear to be part of an emerging ecosystem of lightweight, locally-hosted AI agent platforms, with OpenClaw serving as the foundation and PicoClaw providing an ultra-lightweight alternative for resource-constrained devices.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
